RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Special Weight Purse 43243. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANCHORS AND SPURS was well placed racing just off the top trio entering the turn, hustled up along the rail at the quarter pole then shifted three wide entering the stretch run, steadily advanced down the lane and kicked clear in the final sixteenth. CEL'S STAR hustled up along the rail out of the gate and engaged DAWSON'S STORM for the lead, remained inside and battled on around the turn, gained a slight edge entering the lane then edged away on top leaving the eighth pole, continued to dig in determinedly under firm handling but could not hold off the late gaining winner. DAWSON'S STORM vied outside of CELS STAR for the lead in early stages, battled on two wide around the turn, could not maintain equal terms approaching the furlong marker but remained in striking distance then evened out in late stages. CUPIDS SWEETY vied for the lead racing between foes in opening stages, could not move on with the top pair leaving the backstretch, ran on two wide around the turn, flattened out and ran on evenly in the final furlong. STROLLER BOY raced in the back although never terribly far back in the early going, hustled along three wide around the turn, spun four wide into the lane and ran on one paced.

ENTRY.NAME: Cel's Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: duel inside, shook free, outkicked

ENTRY.NAME: Anchors and Spurs
ENTRY.COMMENT: well placed tracking trio, inside 1/4p, angled 3wd, kicked clear

ENTRY.NAME: Cupids Sweety
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied early btwn, chased 2wd turn, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Dawson's Storm
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied 2wd, evened out

ENTRY.NAME: Stroller Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 3wd turn, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 86. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 17300. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 4, 2022 OR CLAIMING $10,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 4, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRICKBAT was away in good order and settled into tracking position just off the top pair around the first turn, remained well placed sitting just off the top duo up the backstretch, given cue to pick up the pace late on the far turn, roused forward three wide in upper stretch, engaged the top pair for the lead approaching the eighth pole, responded under a drive, gained a narrow advantage over HUNKA BURNIN LOVE then dug in gamely under a drive and drew clear. HUNKA BURNING LOVE sped to the lead in opening stages and led the way around the first turn, quickly came under pressure from SAVAGE entering the backstretch, vied for the lead with rival with a half mile left to run, continued to battle along the inside around the turn, took on the added challenge of BRICKBAIT approaching the eighth pole, fought back gamely into the final furlong then gave way grudgingly. SAVAGE was forwardly placed racing two wide around the first turn, pressed the pace racing under slight restraint into the backstretch, moved up to engage HUNKA BURNIN LOVE for the lead near the half mile marker, battled for command into upper stretch, could not move on past the eighth pole and flattened out. IMINDYCATBIRDSEAT raced three wide into the first turn and settled in the back, came four wide into the lane and had no response when called upon.
